					<p class="">See <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/6.36?lang=eng#35" target="_blank">Doctrine and Covenants 6:36</a>.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote17-13395_000_015"><a name="17-13395_000_015"> </a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote17-13395_000_015">17.</a></span>
					<p class="">Jesus Christ taught us the importance of sacred ordinances, such as baptism (see <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/3.5?lang=eng#4" target="_blank">John 3:5</a>), the sacrament (see <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/59.9?lang=eng#8" target="_blank">Doctrine and Covenants 59:9</a>), and the endowment and sealing ordinances of the temple (see <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/124.39-42?lang=eng#38" target="_blank">Doctrine and Covenants 124:39–42</a>).</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote18-13395_000_015"><a name="18-13395_000_015"> </a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote18-13395_000_015">18.</a></span>
					<p class="">See <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/124.29-32?lang=eng#28" target="_blank">Doctrine and Covenants 124:29–32</a>.</p>
				</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote19-13395_000_015"><a name="19-13395_000_015"> </a>
